imagizer

public java.lang.String imagizer(int width,
                                 int height,
                                 boolean autoCrop)
Generate an Imagizer URL making the image fit into the specified box. The box is defined by width and height. If autoCrop is disable, the image will preserve the original aspect ration. Otherwise it will be cropped to fully fill the space.

Parameters:
width - the image width
height - the image height
autoCrop - enables auto-crop
Returns:
URL

imagizer

public java.lang.String imagizer(int width,
                                 int height,
                                 boolean autoCrop,
                                 int quality,
                                 int filter)
Generate an Imagizer URL making the image fit into the specified box. See imagizer(width, height, autoCrop) for usage. This method allows to apply one of 21 available image filters. filter = 21 will convert the source file to grayscale.

Parameters:
width - the image width
height - the image height
autoCrop - enables auto-crop
quality - integer between 1 and 100
filter - unique image filter
Returns:
URL String URL
